[The hantavirus involved in this cases is probably either New York
virus, Monongahela virus or Sin Nombre virus (SNV). All can cause
hantavirus pulmonary syndrome. The sigmodontine hosts of Sin Nombre
(SNV) and Monongahela viruses is the deer mouse, _Peromyscus
maniculatus_, which is widely distributed in the USA, including Maine.
The white-footed mouse, _P. leucopus_ is also a SNV reservoir. _P.
leucopus_ is the host for New York hantavirus, and is also found in
Maine.

Images of _P. leucopus_ and _P. maniculatus_ can be found at the USA
CDC site, http://www.cdc.gov/hantavirus/rodents/index.html.

Maine can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
http://healthmap.org/r/0Sdy. Somerset County can be seen on the map
at http://www.digital-topo-maps.com/county-map/maine.shtml. -
Mod.TY]
